alert.note: Alert for Coastal Dixie; Coastal Taylor (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Warning issued January 09 at 3:27AM EST until January 10 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 7 AM EST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...Moderate coastal flooding expected. * WHERE...Coastal Taylor and Coastal Dixie Counties. * WHEN...From 7 AM Tuesday to 7 AM EST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Water levels will rise quickly heading into high tide around 2 pm this afternoon. Water levels of 3 to 5 feet above normally dry ground are expected. This will result in moderate flooding of low lying coastal communities like Keaton Beach, Steinhatchee, Horseshoe Beach, and Suwannee. Numerous roads will flood and non-elevated structures will be prone to inundation along the immediate coast. A secondary surge of above normal tides is expected late tonight, though should only be in the 2 to 3 foot above normally dry ground range, primarily affecting coastal roadways.
info.instruction: Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. If travel is required, do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth.
